<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="emperor"><w lemma="αὐτοκράτωρ">Α<unclear reason="damage">ὐ</unclear>τοκράτορα</w>  <lb n="2"/><name nymRef="#Καῖσαρ">Καίσαρα</name>  <name nymRef="#Μᾶρκος">Μᾶρ  <lb n="3" break="no"/>κον</name>  <name nymRef="#Αὐρήλιος">Αὐρήλιον</name>  <lb n="4"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <name nymRef="#Σεουῆρος">Σεουῆρον</name>    <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="5"/><name nymRef="#Ἀντωνεῖνος">Ἀντωνεῖνον</name><lb n="6"/><name nymRef="#Εὐσεβής">Εὐσεβῆ</name>  <name nymRef="#Σεβαστός">Σε<lb n="7" break="no"/>βαστὸν</name>  <w lemma="βρεταννικός">Βρε<lb n="8" break="no"/>τα<hi rend="ligature">νν</hi>ικὸν</w>  <w lemma="μέγας">Μέ<lb n="9" break="no"/>γιστον</w></persName>  <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w>  <w lemma="δῆμος">δῆ<lb n="10" break="no"/>μος</w>  <w lemma="ἐκ">ἐξ</w>  <w lemma="ἀπόλειψις">ἀπο<lb n="11" break="no"/>λείψεως</w>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Φλάβιος">Φλα<lb n="12" break="no"/>βίου</name>  <name nymRef="#Ἄτταλος">Ἀττάλου</name>  </persName><lb n="12a"/><space unit="line" extent="1" dim="vertical"/>    <lb n="13"/><w lemma="ἐπιμελέω">ἐπιμεληθέντος</w>  <g ref="#stop"/>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μᾶρκος"><expan><abbr>Μάρ</abbr><ex>κου</ex></expan></name>  <g ref="#stop"/>  <name nymRef="#Αὐρήλιος"><expan><abbr>Αὐρ</abbr><ex>ηλίου</ex></expan></name>    <lb n="14"/>  <name nymRef="#Χρήσιμος">Χρησίμου</name>  <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἀπολλώνιος">Ἀπολλωνίου</name></persName></persName></ab>
</div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>l. 1, first two letters damaged; <foreign xml:lang="grc">Α</foreign> is clearly legible but <foreign xml:lang="grc">Υ</foreign> is not.</p>
            <p>l. 14, the final <foreign xml:lang="grc">Υ</foreign> is tall.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Imperator Caesar Marcus Aurelius Severus Antoninus Pius Augustus, Britannicus Maximus. The People <supplied reason="subaudible">put up his statue</supplied> from the bequest of Flavius Attalos. Marcus Aurelius Chresimos, son of Apollonios, undertook <supplied reason="subaudible">care of the erection</supplied>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>This text must have accompanied a statue of Caracalla, whose name included the element Britannicus from 210 A.D.</p>
            <p> Another statue of Julia Domna (<ref type="inscription" n="1309" target="120642.xml"/>=MAMA 452) which is a pair to this, was found in the same area; a further statue of Caracalla (<ref type="inscription" n="1308" target="120326.xml"/>=MAMA 451) was set up from the same bequest.</p>
            <p>The epimelete is not otherwise known at present.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography" n="none">
            <p>Unpublished.</p>
         </div>
